She is everything I didn’t know I needed…. 

Let me just share a quick story with you guys.

As I was transitioning in my career, maybe right at the start ….Pastor @juanitarasmus would always ask me “what would you love?”

I didn’t know how the hell to answer that, and my answer was ya know….something basic …. 

Her asking me that (and regularly) was the start of me seeing that whatever I thought or said I would love , would actually become !

I then read her book, “Learning To Be”, : Finding your center after the bottom falls out . 

IT CHANGED MY THOUGHT PATTERN.

In this book she gave a glimpse of what she calls the “crash”, her experience with depression.

Y’all …. It’s a good book Frfr . 
She bares it all. 
Her transparency is what made me keep turning the pages !

I would encourage anyone who is a type 1 on the enneagram…. A perfectionists….or like me a type () - I won’t tell you until you meet us on the 31st of this month , then this book is for you !

Pastor Juanita, thank you for teaching me how to be open and willing to receive and to give love 🙆🏽‍♀️

Thank you for your patience with me.

When I am with you , I am a student in your presence.

I thank God for your being. #HappyWomensHistoryMonth

Ladies and gentlemen come purchase a book and get a signed copy from Pastor @juanitarasmus on Friday March 31, 2023 @stjohnsdowntownhouston from 6PM-8PM.

Check out her website at www.Juanita Rasmus.com for more information.

Thank You South Texas College of Law Houston for the invitation to attend your 100th Year Celebration, while also welcoming Michael F. Barry as the 11th President and Dean of the school !
It was an honor to represent @amazing102.5fmhtx Powered by @breadoflifehtx 

What a wonderful ceremony ❤️

South Texas College of Law Houston — Houston’s oldest law school — highlighted 100 years of excellence in legal education during its April 13 Centennial Founder’s Day Celebration.

“STCL Houston has been a significant contributor to Houston and to Texas for 100 years,” said President and Dean Michael F. Barry. “More than 16,000 legal professionals – federal and state appellate and trial judges, litigators and transactional attorneys, prosecutors and defense counsel, corporate counsel and public interest attorneys, and leaders in government and in industry – credit South Texas with preparing them for a lifetime of successful practice and service. We look forward to your presence to help us mark this momentous occasion.”
As the program began at 9 a.m., STCL Houston Board of Director Chair Genora K. Boykins ’85 welcomed guests. The event’s highlight was Dean Barry’s state of the law school multi-media presentation, “STCL at 100.” He is STCL Houston’s 11th dean.
Special proclamations was presented by Texas Supreme Court Chief Justice Nathan L. Hecht, U.S. Representative Sheila Jackson Lee, Harris County Commissioner Rodney Ellis, City Councilman Robert Gallegos, and Mayor Sylvester Turner. Other guest speakers included U.S. Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals Judge Jennifer Walker Elrod, State Bar of Texas President Laura Gibson, YMCA of Greater Houston President and CEO Stephen Ives, Executive Director Betty Balli Torres of the Texas Access to Justice Foundation, Baylor Law Dean Bradley J.B. Toben, and Vinson & Elkins Partner David Oelman — the great-grandnephew of STCL Houston’s founding dean, and the Honorable Joseph C. Hutcheson, Jr.

What are 3 words to describe you today ?

I’ve asked countless guests this same question.
The one word I have heard more than others is “RESILIENT”.

re·sil·ient
/rəˈzilēənt/
adjective
adjective: resilient

Resilient: (adjective) able to withstand or recover quickly from difficult conditions. As we face challenges and hardships, it is our ability to cope, adapt, and bounce back that defines us.

Today, I embody resilience—a quality that empowers me to thrive in the face of adversity. I embrace the lessons learned from difficult experiences, using them as stepping stones toward growth and success. Resilience fuels my determination and strengthens my resolve to overcome any obstacle on my path.

Remember, it's not about avoiding hardships, but how we respond to them that shapes our journey. Let's embrace our inner resilience and inspire others to do the same. Together, we can achieve greatness. 💫 #Resilience #Adaptability #Growth"

My three words to describe me today are 
* RESILIENT 
* DETERMINED 
* FOCUSED
What’s yours ?

HERE’S MORE ABOUT DIAMONDS AND PEARLS.
The Diamonds and Pearls Senior Citizens Program is a notable initiative hosted by St. John's Downtown. This program brings together senior citizens on a monthly basis, specifically on the third Wednesday of each month. Its primary objective is to provide a platform for fostering spiritual growth, offering support, and enhancing the overall well-being of its senior members and friends.

The program is designed to equip senior individuals with valuable tools and discussions that enable them to navigate the complexities of modern technology through our partnership with Bread of Life Inc’s., #TechSavvySeniorHOU initiative; while also encouraging active participation within the larger community. The Diamonds and Pearls Senior Citizens Program invites seniors who seek not only to enrich their lives through shared experiences but also to stay connected, engaged, and empowered in an ever-evolving world.

You can be a partner too !
Decide to be apart of the movement by contributing your time, talent, or your funds by going online to www.breadoflifeinc.org

The CORE 100 is our annual list of the most influential Blacks today. It’s our way of honoring champions who changed the game by transforming people, policy or practices through their leadership. These 100 distinguished individuals are inspirational as they currently remove barriers, which paves the way for generations to come. This list of honorees is a mark to and reminder of the beauty, boldness, and brilliance of Blackness, at a time when the cultural, economic, and political landscape has grown ever more hostile to Black excellence. Let’s all salute and pay homage to the 2024 class of CORE 100!

This is me 15 pounds lighter after going vegetarian 🥗 🥑 🌱 6 months ago 😘

I was so determined to do a lifestyle change, and also try something new.

Some of the challenges I’ve faced are:
* at-home meals that don’t taste good or aren’t fulfilling
(I sometimes feel like I’m never full)
* no variety menu options at restaurants 
* being with friends/family that tell me repeatedly with their tone getting louder with each expression 
🗣️YOU DON’T EAT MEAT?

BENEFITS
* weight loss 
* mental clarity 
* discipline 
* enthusiasm to try new foods

I have more work to do 🤞🏾💪🏾
